WEBVTT

0
00:00:03.190 --> 00:00:04.969
What's the chance of rolling snake eyes?

1
00:00:05.769 --> 00:00:08.539
What's the chance of flipping heads 3 times in a row?

2
00:00:09.460 --> 00:00:13.000
When calculating the probability of 2 or more events happening together,

3
00:00:13.460 --> 00:00:15.819
we can use the multiplication rule of probability.

4
00:00:16.719 --> 00:00:19.510
We'll start with independent events where one event's outcome

5
00:00:19.510 --> 00:00:21.860
has no effect on the other event's outcome.

6
00:00:22.469 --> 00:00:23.389
For example,

7
00:00:23.719 --> 00:00:26.149
what's the probability of rolling snake eyes?

8
00:00:26.479 --> 00:00:28.379
Each roll is an independent event

9
00:00:28.680 --> 00:00:32.720
because the value on one die has no influence on the value of the second die.

10
00:00:34.299 --> 00:00:38.049
The multiplication rule of probability says that the probability of two events,

11
00:00:38.099 --> 00:00:38.659
A and B,

12
00:00:38.740 --> 00:00:39.720
happening together

13
00:00:40.020 --> 00:00:41.819
is the probability of event A

14
00:00:42.020 --> 00:00:42.799
multiplied

15
00:00:42.909 --> 00:00:44.979
by the probability of event B.

16
00:00:45.180 --> 00:00:45.799
In this case,

17
00:00:46.299 --> 00:00:48.740
the probability of rolling a 1 on the first die

18
00:00:48.950 --> 00:00:52.099
multiplied by the probability of rolling a 1 on the second die.

19
00:00:52.900 --> 00:00:55.049
This is the case if you're rolling the dice together

20
00:00:55.380 --> 00:00:56.840
or one at a time.

21
00:00:57.220 --> 00:00:59.619
The probability of rolling a 1 on a die

22
00:00:59.860 --> 00:01:01.119
is 1 out of 6,

23
00:01:01.369 --> 00:01:03.779
so the probability of rolling a 1 on both dice

24
00:01:03.979 --> 00:01:06.339
is 1/6 times 1/6

25
00:01:06.660 --> 00:01:07.120
or

26
00:01:07.330 --> 00:01:08.739
1 out of 36.

27
00:01:09.550 --> 00:01:12.459
Across all 36 possible rolls of 2 dice,

28
00:01:12.839 --> 00:01:13.379
one of them

29
00:01:13.639 --> 00:01:14.500
is snake eyes.

30
00:01:15.809 --> 00:01:17.260
Let's look at a second example.

31
00:01:17.529 --> 00:01:20.529
What's the probability of flipping heads 3 times in a row?

32
00:01:20.889 --> 00:01:21.360
Well,

33
00:01:21.650 --> 00:01:24.269
it's the probability of the first flip landing heads

34
00:01:24.529 --> 00:01:25.309
multiplied

35
00:01:25.569 --> 00:01:28.029
by the probability of the 2nd flip landing heads

36
00:01:28.239 --> 00:01:28.949
multiplied

37
00:01:29.050 --> 00:01:31.750
by the probability of the 3rd flip landing heads.

38
00:01:32.129 --> 00:01:34.809
1/2 times 1/2 x 1/22,

39
00:01:35.370 --> 00:01:36.089
1/8.